This document explains how to create a Run Analysis Report to streamline mechanical Run Debug Checklist steps and visualize in UI to get insight to both customer and us.

This report is generated using SQL stored procedures and is integrated into a Tableau dashboard for visualization.

Whenever a new run is triggered, the `CreateRunAnalysisReport` stored procedure is automatically executed as part of the post-process pipeline via the `RunPostProcessQueries` procedure. This ensures that analysis results are always up-to-date and available without manual intervention:

```
CREATE PROCEDURE [markdown].[RunPostProcessQueries]
(
    @RunId INT = 0
)
AS
BEGIN
    EXEC [report].[RefreshRunReports] @RunId = @RunId;
    EXEC [report].[BenchmarkReport] @RunId = @RunId;
    EXEC [FibaReporting].[report].[CreateRunAnalysisReport] @RunId = @RunId;
    EXEC [FibaReporting].[report].[CreateComplianceReport] @RunId = @RunId;
END;
```

